Version Date: 2012-10-26Version Text: 2012-10-26Version Date: 2012-10-26Version Text: 2012-10-26 Subject: null  Type: null  Notes: The ASCII data for this collection have been completely replaced. The data collection has been updated to include SAS, SPSS, and Stata setup files for use with the new data. Also included in the update are a corresponding SAS transport (CPORT) file, SPSS system file, Stata system file, and a tab-delimited version of the new ASCII data.;Subject: Study Level Error Note, Notes: The 2003 wave of the Tobacco Use Supplement is comprised of data from this collection, along with data collected in February 2003 (ICPSR 4526) and June 2003 (ICPSR 4527). It is recommended that all three files be used when analyzing the data at the state level. It is also important to use all three files when trying to replicate analysis done by the National Cancer Institute, as much of their analysis was based on a statistical average of all three months.;Subject: Study Level Error Note, Notes: <p>For additional information about past, current, and future National Cancer Institute (NCI) Tobacco Use Supplements and data products and publications utilizing supplement data, see the NCI Web site
<a href="http://riskfactor.cancer.gov/studies/tus-cps/">http://riskfactor.cancer.gov/studies/tus-cps/</a>
.</p>;Subject: Study Level Error Note, Notes: Users are strongly encouraged to refer to the User Guide (produced by the Principal Investigators), which contains not only information about the basic CPS survey, but also detailed technical documentation specific to the Tobacco Use Supplement. In particular, Attachment 8 of the User Guide contains the supplement questionnaire.;Subject: Study Level Error Note, Notes: Edited universe statements for various variables are defined in either the basic or supplement record layout, which are located in Attachments 6 and 7, respectively, of the User Guide.;Subject: Study Level Error Note, Notes: ICPSR removed all FILLER and PADDING variables from the data. As a result, the column locations in any ICPSR-released data product (e.g., codebook and setup files) will have column locations that are not consistent with locations described in the User Guide.; Subject: null  Type: null  Notes: Stata system file(s), sav Data file(s), stc Data file(s), tsv Data file(s), Data file(s), and electronic documentation.;
